com.itko.lisa.test

Interface FilterInterface

  • All Superinterfaces:
    com.itko.util.test.FilterInterface, com.itko.lisa.model.IWriteXML, NamedType, java.io.Serializable

    public interface FilterInterface
extends com.itko.util.test.FilterInterface, com.itko.lisa.model.IWriteXML, java.io.Serializable, NamedType
    NOTE: Filters should now extend FilterBaseImpl.java and implement subPreFilter and subPostFilter methods

    Filters are used to do any kind of result parsing or custom validation you might require. There are several filters that come with LISA, such as the FilterXMLGetTagAttribute, which uses the SAX XML parser to find a particular value in a result to store as a property. However, most of the Filters you will use for HTML processing are listed below

    They are expressed as XML fragments in a test case document. The only required attribute that is set is the type, for example: 

     <Filter> type="com.itko.lisa.FilterGetAttribute"/>

    Filters can be placed either as a direct child of the TestCase itself, in which case the filter will execute on every node that is not set to ignore filters, or at the Node level in which case the filter will fire every time that node is executed. TestCase level nodes are executed first, then Node level ones.

    See Also:
    FilterVectorOfTags, FilterGetAttribute, FilterXMLGetTagAttribute

        Parameters:
        e - is the XML DOM for the Filter
        Throws:
        TestDefException - when you cannot under any circumstances work

      • preFilter

        boolean preFilter(TestExec ts)
                  throws TestRunException
        This method is called by LISA after the currently executing TestNode has prepared for the test Node's actual execution but before so doing. This is your opporunity to contribute to the Node setup. For example, you might need to prepare your filter's state based on what parameters are going to be sent to the server, or you might want to modify or set a particular property value that will be used in the actual data to send to the server.

        Parameters:
        ts - is the TestExec (test execution object) that holds the current state.

        Returns:
        true to allow test node execution to continue false means there was some kind of error, so don't execute the node. if this happens, then the next node in the workflow will be executed. You could set this node before returning false by calling TestExec.setNextNode( String nodeName )

        Throws:
        TestRunException - when you need to report some kind of fatal error that should halt test execution

        See Also:
        TestExec

      • postFilter

        boolean postFilter(TestExec ts)
                   throws TestRunException
        This method is called on your filter after execution of the TestNode's custom "execute()" method. The result of the node execution is available, so any parsing or custom validation that need be done can be performed here.

        Parameters:
        ts - for the TestExec (our state)
        Returns:
        true to continue test node execution normally false to interrupt test node execution see preFilter() for discussion about how and why to do that.

        Throws:
        TestRunException - when you need to report some kind of fatal error that should halt test execution

        See Also:
        TestExec
